  <groups>
    <fields>
      <fieldname>gid</fieldname>
      <fieldname>sid</fieldname>
      <fieldname>group_name</fieldname>
      <fieldname>group_order</fieldname>
      <fieldname>description</fieldname>
      <fieldname>language</fieldname>
    </fields>
    <rows>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[18]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 1]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[0]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[This example shows some of the options that can be set for list (radio) questions. In the second question, <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#random_order">random answer order</a> is turned on, and the answer options are shown in a random order. The third question has &quot;<a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#hide_tip">hide tip</a>&quot; on, meaning it will not show the line that says &quot;Choose one of the following answers.&quot;]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[19]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 2]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[1]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[&nbsp;This example shows some of the attributes that can be set for multiple numerical input questions. The second question has <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#slider_layout">slider layout</a> on, so the boxes are replaced with sliders. the <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#slider_min">slider minimum</a>, <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#slider_max">slider maximum</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#slider_accuracy">slider accuracy</a>&nbsp;are also set. The third question has a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#min_num_value">minimum</a> and <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#max_num_value">maximum sum</a> set.]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[20]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 3]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[2]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[This example shows some of the attributes that can be set for text questions. In the second question, the <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#text_input_width">text input width</a>&nbsp;and <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#maximum_chars">maximum characters</a> are set, specifying how wide the text box should be and how many characters it can contain. In the third question, a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#prefix">prefix</a> and <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#suffix">suffix</a> are set, which appear right before and after the text box (useful for fill in the blank questions).]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[21]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 4a]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[3]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[This example demonstrates the use of the timer attributes. The following huge text box has a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#time_limit">time limit</a> set to 30 (seconds), and a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#time_limit_action">time limit action</a> set to &quot;disable only,&quot; which makes the text box read-only after the time limit expires. Also, a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#time_limit_message">time limit message</a> is set and will show when the time limit has expired.]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[22]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 5]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[5]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[This example shows some of the attributes that can be set for date questions. In the second question, a <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#dropdown_dates_year_min">minimum</a> and <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#dropdown_dates_year_max">maximum year</a> are set, so the user can only choose dates within the specified years. In the third question, &quot;<a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#dropdown_dates">Display Select Boxes</a>&quot; is turned on, which changes the appearance of the question.]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[23]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 6]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[6]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[This example shows some of the attributes that can be set for multiple options (checkboxes) questions. In both questions, an <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#exclude_all_others">exclusive option</a> is set. This means that if the exclusive option is clicked, all of the other options will automatically deselect and be disabled. In the second question, <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#min_answers">minimum</a> and <a href="http://docs.limesurvey.org/tiki-index.php?page=Question+attributes&amp;structure=English+Instructions+for+LimeSurvey#max_answers">maximum answers</a> are set, so that the user can only submit the survey when there is at least one but no more than 3 boxes checked.]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
      <row>
        <gid><![CDATA[26]]></gid>
        <sid><![CDATA[33263]]></sid>
        <group_name><![CDATA[Example 4b]]></group_name>
        <group_order><![CDATA[4]]></group_order>
        <description><![CDATA[此區塊示範計時器屬性：下方題目限制 60 秒，時間到後不警告直接跳下一步，並在剩 30 秒與 10 秒時各顯示 3 秒提示訊息。]]></description>
        <language>zh-Hant-TW</language>
      </row>
    </rows>
  </groups>
